message.content: Cross-multiplying, we have $(x-4)(x-9)=36$. Since we are looking for positive values of $x$, looking at the quadratic we can see that swapping $x-4$ and $x-9$ makes the quadratic increase. Thus, we look for a factor pair close to the average of 4 and 9, namely 6, and find a solution of $\boxed{10}$.
